The paper focuses on the optimization of activation functions in deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the impact of activation functions on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of automatic search techniques and reinforcement learning-based search could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the discovered activation function could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) if the evaluation involves natural language processing tasks.
